# dp[i][s]: the max length of the billboard that can be supported by rods[:i] with sum s
        # dp[i][s] = max(dp[i-1][s], dp[i-1][s-rods[i]] + rods[i])
        # initial: dp[0][0] = 0, dp[0][s] = 0
        # answer: dp[len(rods)][0]
        dp = [[0] * (sum(rods) + 1) for _ in range(len(rods) + 1)]
        for i in range(1, len(rods) + 1):
            for s in range(sum(rods) + 1):
                dp[i][s] = dp[i-1][s]
                if s >= rods[i-1]:
                    dp[i][s] = max(dp[i][s], dp[i-1][s-rods[i-1]] + rods[i-1])
        return dp[len(rods)][0]
